metadata.title: File
metadata.description: Mapping GDC file to FHIR. GDC file is a set of related records (either written or electronic) kept together. (NCIt C42883)

source.name: file

destination.name: DocumentReference
destination.description: A reference to a document of any kind for any purpose. While the term “document” implies a more narrow focus, for this resource this "document" encompasses any serialized object with a mime-type, it includes formal patient-centric documents (CDA), clinical notes, scanned paper, non-patient specific documents like policy text, as well as a photo, video, or audio recording acquired or used in healthcare. The DocumentReference resource provides metadata about the document so that the document can be discovered and managed. The actual content may be inline base64 encoded data or provided by direct reference.

source.name: file_name
source.description: The name (or part of a name) of a file (of any type).

destination.title: Label to display in place of the data
